00:47:21.630 --> 00:47:25.172
That's the lowest vacant,
the lowest unoccupied

00:47:25.172 --> 00:47:26.510
molecular orbital.
 

00:47:26.510 --> 00:47:32.409
And if we rotate it here,
you can see the inner part.

00:47:32.409 --> 00:47:35.860
And bear in mind that there are
two spherical nodes.

00:47:35.860 --> 00:47:40.347
There's one that's really tiny,
that's inside anything we can

00:47:40.347 --> 00:47:41.170
see here.
 

00:47:41.170 --> 00:47:44.233
Okay, then there's this
orbital, which is the

00:47:44.233 --> 00:47:47.434
