looked at from a funny angle

00:47:47.434 --> 00:47:50.289
where it's not very clear what
it is.

00:47:50.289 --> 00:47:56.027
But if we rotate all these by
90°, you can see that it's

00:47:56.027 --> 00:47:59.918
like that cross,
or whatever you call it,

00:47:59.918 --> 00:48:02.739
of the 3d_x^2-y^2.
 

00:48:02.739 --> 00:48:05.130
But why doesn't it look just
like that?

00:48:05.130 --> 00:48:06.980
Why are they distorted?
 

00:48:06.980 --> 00:48:09.760
Why does it have this funny
U-shape here.

00:48:09.760 --> 00:48:13.231
Instead of this lobe,
this lobe, here and here,

00:48:13.231 --> 00:48:15.269
the lobes moved up there.
 

00:48:15.269 --> 00:48:17.309
Why?
 

00:48:17.309 --> 00:48:18.179
Angela?
 

00:48:18.179 --> 00:48:18.849
Pardon me?
 

00:48:18.849 --> 00:48:19.570
Student:  There are
protons.

00:48:19.570 --> 00:48:21.693
Prof: That's where the
protons pulled them,

00:48:21.693 --> 00:48:22.690
the potential energy.
 

00:48:22.690 --> 00:48:26.010
But the fundamental shape,
before it got distorted by the

00:48:26.010 --> 00:48:28.679
